Minister of Public Enterprises Pravin Gordhan is expected to release a Special Paper on Eskom on Tuesday. The document will detail a comprehensive road-map for the struggling state-owned entity. Editor's note: Livestream courtesy DStv 403, you can also watch it on DStv Now. JOHANNESBURG - Minister of Public Enterprises Pravin Gordhan is expected to release a Special Paper on Eskom on Tuesday. The document will detail a comprehensive road-map for the struggling state-owned entity.
At the same time, the Standing Committee on Appropriations will be briefed by Eskom’s Executive Board. WATCH : Gordhan, Malema hate speech case showdown Last week the Special Appropriations Bill was passed in Parliament. The bill will give Eskom a R59-billion bailout once approved by the National Council of Provinces. Although Eskom has not implemented load shedding for over a week, the power utility warns the system remains vulnerable and any unexpected shift may result in load-shedding at short notice.